CS Courses: Algorithms, Architecture, OS, Data Science, Neural Networks, Computer Vision
Qualities of a good summary: It should have information about the I/O
Qualities of a bad summary: Not readable. Complex and unnecessary details
1-3 unimportant details: complex processing of information inside the function body

Qualities of a good summary: Short, concise and to the point
Qualities of a bad summary: very lengthy and doesn’t explain the overall use of code.
1-3 important details: 1. use of variables and what they mean. 2. Description of  algorithms. 3.overall use of the method and when its called
1-3 unimportant details: summary of each line in the code. Description of various methods being used in the code.

Qualities of a good summary: Concise sentence that explains internal functions
Qualities of a bad summary: summary that just repeats the class name
1-3 important details: class name, input parameters, return type
1-3 unimportant details: error and exception handling, print messages

Qualities of a good summary: Concise but also has enough information to help the reader understand the code
Qualities of a bad summary: Too lengthy or short. Incorrect or irrelevant information
1-3 important details: What variables the code is changing and why? High-level idea of what the code is doing.
1-3 unimportant details: How exactly the code is structured

Qualities of a good summary: Describes the main task of the method
Qualities of a bad summary: missing the I/O of the method
1-3 important details: I/O and special conditions about the function

Other Coding Languages: C, C++, Python, Javascript, PHP, Perl, Bash
Qualities of a good summary: Describes what the code does and why it is used but omits details of the “how” that are encapsulated within the code
Qualities of a bad summary: Simply regurgitating information that is already obvious from the name of the method. Uses overly technical, vague, poorly defined jargon
1-3 important details: What are the inputs and what do they mean? What is being modified and what is read-only? What was the programmer trying to do when they wrote the code?
1-3 unimportant details: Variable and types when it is obvious from naming conventions. Algorithmic details, unless they are about the algorithm time/space complexity.

Qualities of a good summary: Example Usage, I/O, Variable types and constraints. Succinct without missing functionality. Grammatically Correct.
Qualities of a bad summary: Long, verbose, line by line summaries, repetitive functionality, poorly attributed variables, unimportant details of rationale of the “why” for logical choices
1-3 important details: Variables with associated types. Clear inputs and Outputs. Clear constrains and limits
1-3 unimportant details: Attributes of Non-input variables. Explanation of each and every line

Qualities of a good summary: It should talk about the primary motive of the code
Qualities of a bad summary: it talks about the wrong motive or talks about some sub-detail and misses the main point.
1-3 important details: It should include the objective of the code and the broad sub-cases in which it might fail to work.
1-3 unimportant details: The summary does not need to talk about the exact conditions and initialization values in the code.

Qualities of a good summary: Written in easy to read english, contains information not in the function name
1-3 important details: What is its function, What are the inputs and outputs. Error States Maybe?
